NATP Module 10 Dry-Run Plan: Vital Signs
Current Dry-Run Model

This dry run includes only NATP Module 10: Vital Signs.

This is a source-first test package for the future 24-hour CNA Recertification Theory Class. It is not the full class. It does not include NATP Modules 11-17, final assessment planning, certificate issuance, or optional clinical support completion.

Module 10 Scope

Learner-facing title: NATP Module 10: Vital Signs
Theory time for dry run: 3 hours / 180 minutes
Source-recommended clinical time: 6 hours, tracked as in-person or evaluator-supported only, not online credit
Instructional source: cccco-na-model-curriculum-module-10.pdf as source-file history only
Learner-facing source label: NATP Module 10: Vital Signs

Source Purpose

The module prepares learners to know how, when, and why vital signs are taken, how to report and chart vital-sign procedures, how to measure temperature, pulse, respirations, and blood pressure, and how to recognize and report normal and abnormal findings.

Module 10 Objectives

NATP Module 10 contains these 16 objectives: define terminology; describe vital signs and observations; discuss temperature; describe measures to raise/lower body temperature; describe pulse and pulse sites; describe pulse factors and qualities; define respiration; describe respiration observations; describe abnormal breathing patterns; describe TPR as a combined procedure; explain blood pressure; identify BP factors; identify BP equipment; discuss BP procedure; discuss pain observation/reporting; and record vital signs on charts, graphs, and Nursing Assistant notes.

Delivery Model

Use a MediaLessonPlayer as the core shell. Each objective is a chapter. Every objective gets:

one short media/slide segment;
one mobile-friendly exercise;
one quick knowledge or decision check;
one source trace note;
one completion event.

Hands-on procedures are shown as demonstration and checklist support only. The app must not say the learner has demonstrated hands-on competency online.

